texture data: DRILLING BRECCIA, BRECCIA IS COMPOSED OF CLAY-SIZE (POSSIBLY COMMINUTED MINERALS) IN A MATRIX WITH A COARSE FRACTION (APPROXIMATELY 50 PERCENT) WHICH VARIES FROM FINE TO VERY COARSE SAND - THIS COARSE FRACTION CONTAINS MICA SCHIST (65 PERCENT) + GLAUCONITE (15 PERCENT) + VEIN QTZ OR QUARTZITE (15 PERCENT) + GLAUCONITE SANDSTONE (5 PERCENT) - MOST FRAGMENTS ARE ANGULAR BUT SOME QTZ GRAINS ARE ROUNDED, INTERVALS (18-47 CM) AND (120-129 CM) ARE THE SAME AS THE REST OF THE SECTION BUT HAVE NO COARSE FRACTION
